      About this item

      • WORLDWIDE ADAPTER - Our all-in-one adapter includes 4 different plugs that cover over 200 countries and regions, such as USA, Canada, Japan, UK, Ireland, Scotland, France, Germany, Italy, Spain, China, Australia, Argentina, New Zealand, etc. (excluding South Africa, India).
      • 6 IN 1 TRAVEL ADAPTER - Charge up to 6 devices simultaneously at high speed with 4 USB-A ports (2.4A), 1 USB-C port (3A), and 1 AC socket. Ideal for charging iPhones, laptops, tablets, power banks, cameras, headsets, and more.
      • SAFETY CERTIFIED - This travel adapter is equipped with built-in 10A fuse, safety shutters and plug lock system. In addition, it is certified by RoHS, CE, and FCC, ensuring its safety and reliability.
      • NOT A VOLTAGE CONVERTER - This universal power adapter does not convert voltage and may not be suitable for use with high-power appliances like hair dryers, curling irons, straighteners, and other similar devices. Max Power: 1100W at 110V, 2400W at 240V.
      • SATISFACTION SERVICE - 30 days money-back and if there's anything wrong with the adapter, we will fix the problem for free or send you a new replacement by default (2-Year Limited). Please contact us if you have any questions, we will reply you within 24 hours and provide you with a satisfactory solution.
      • TIPS - If you need more fuses, you can search for "Epicka replacement fuse" on Amazon for purchasing. Please ensure that you're selecting Epicka's 10A fuses, as using fuses with incorrect specifications could lead to incompatibility with the product.

      • Can the adapter be used for a hair dryer?

        It depends on the type of hair dryer you are using. In short, only hair dryers labeled with specifications like "100-240V, 50/60Hz" and with a power rating of less than 2000W can be used in countries with 220-240V power supply, such as in Europe.

      • The AC outlet of the adapter wouldn't work anymore, how to process it?

        This is likely due to a blown fuse. You can pry open the compartment at the bottom of the adapter (labeled as "SPARE & FUSE") and replace the fuse. If it still doesn't work, please email Epicka for further assistance.

      • Can I charge my laptop in Europe through the Epicka adapter? Does it need a converter?

        Yes, most laptops support dual voltage (with 100-240V, 50/60Hz printed on it). You can use our Epicka adapter to charge your laptop without the need for a voltage converter even in a country with 220-240V power apply.

      • Planning trips to South Africa & India, but TA-105 adapter doesn't fit. Does EPICKA have adapters for these countries?

        Yes, we have a new adapter model X232 that is suitable for South Africa and India. Please search "EPICKA X232 adapter" on Amazon and choose Type D for India and Type M for South Africa.

      • How can I purchase additional fuses?

        You can search for "EPICKA Replacement Fuse" on Amazon to purchase extra fuses. Please ensure that you're selecting Epicka's 10A fuses, as fuses with incorrect specifications might not be compatible with the product.

      How customer reviews and ratings work

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      • jeff
        5.0 out of 5 stars Incredible Product
        Reviewed in the United States on October 20, 2024
        Item Package Quantity: 1Color: GreyVerified Purchase
        This review is for the TA105 Epicka universal travel adapter. I have been traveling to Europe, Australia, Mexico and South America. I have been going on Rick Steves tours which suggest packing light. Typical hotel rooms have only one or two outlets. Cruise ships also have very few outlets. My wife and I are always fighting over the outlets. When I travel I have 1. ) hearing aide charger, 2.) watch charger, 3.) phone charger 4.) CPAP machine 5.)iPad and 6.) Kindle. This travel adapter will let me keep all my electronics charged. I thought that in the future more electronics would require a USB type C. I was surprised to find this product included two usb A to usb type C plugs giving me the option of charging three batteries with usb type C plugs. I was also pleased to find a soft case to pack the travel adapter in was included. Epicka sent me an email pointing out that a 2000 watt hair dryer would over load the travel adapter. Note, this unit does not change the incoming voltage. Other countries use different voltages so you need to check your products to ensure they can handle the voltage of the country you are in.

        Attached are photographs of the product with the instructions and warnings. When I purchased this product I did not realize that it included a carrying case, extra fuses, easy to follow instructions and two usb A to usb to C adapters. A nice bonus.
